The paper is about network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes the use of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks and feature embedding for improved performance, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of categorical information, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with network traffic data, which can be considered a type of sensor data, and thus falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
